Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharp turn. Clay near fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 52, 1 Name Alexiadas. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 191.10.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1009)
